1) Project Definition

Definition :-A software project is a temporary effort to design, develop, test, and deliver a software product within given time, cost, and scope.

It has:
A start and end date
A specific goal
Limited resources (time, cost, people)

💡 Example

👉 Example: Online Food Delivery App
Goal: Build an app like Zomato
Start Date: 1 Jan 2026
End Date: 30 June 2026
Team: Developers, designers, testers
Features: Login, restaurant listing, order system, payment

2) Contract Management (Software Project Management)

defination :-Contract Management is the process of creating, managing, and controlling agreements (contracts) between a client and a software development company.

It ensures that:
Work is done as per agreement
Payment, timeline, and scope are followed properly

💡 Example

👉 A company hires a software firm to build an app like Swiggy
Client: Restaurant company
Vendor: Software development company
Contract includes:
Cost: ₹5,00,000
Time: 4 months
Features: Order system, payment, tracking

➡️ Contract Management ensures:
Work is delivered on time
Payment is done as per milestones
Any changes are properly handled

3) Activities Covered by Software Project Management

defination :-Software Project Management (SPM) includes all activities required to plan, execute, monitor, and complete a software project successfully.

🔑 Main Activities:-

1. 📋 Project Planning
Define goals, scope, and requirements
Create project plan (time, cost, resources)
👉 Example: Planning features for an app like Zomato

2. ⏳ Scheduling
Decide timeline and deadlines
Use tools like Gantt chart

3. 💰 Cost Estimation
Estimate total budget
Calculate cost of developers, tools, etc.

4. 👥 Resource Management
Assign team members (developers, testers)
Manage workload

5. ⚠️ Risk Management
Identify possible risks (delay, bugs)
Plan solutions

6. 🧪 Quality Management
Ensure software meets standards
Testing and reviews

7. 📊 Project Monitoring & Control
Track progress
Compare planned vs actual work

8. 🔄 Change Management
Handle changes in requirements
Update plans accordingly

9. 📢 Communication Management
Share updates with team and client
Meetings, reports

10. 📦 Project Closure
Deliver final product
Documentation and review

4) Overview of Project Planning

defination :-Project Planning is the process of defining project goals, scope, schedule, resources, and cost to ensure successful software development.
-> It is the first and most important step, because a good plan helps avoid delays, extra cost, and failures.

💡 Example

👉 Planning a food delivery app like Zomato
Decide features: Login, search, order, payment
Timeline: 5 months
Budget: ₹6,00,000
Team: 5 developers + 2 testers
➡️ This complete preparation before development is Project Planning

🔑 Main Steps in Project Planning
1. 🎯 Define Objectives
What is the goal of the project?

2. 📦 Define Scope
What is included and excluded?

3. 📅 Scheduling
Timeline and deadlines

4. 💰 Cost Estimation
Budget planning

5. 👥 Resource Planning
Team and tools required

6. ⚠️ Risk Planning
Identify possible problems

7. 📊 Quality Planning
Set quality standards 

🎯 Importance of Project Planning
Reduces risk
Saves time and cost
Improves quality
Ensures clear direction 

5) Stepwise Project Planning

Definition :-Stepwise Project Planning is a systematic process of planning a project by dividing it into clear steps from objectives to execution.

🔢 Steps in Stepwise Project Planning

1. 🎯 Identify Project Scope & Objectives
Define what the project will achieve
👉 Example: Build an app like Swiggy

2. 📌 Identify Project Infrastructure
Decide tools, technology, hardware, software

3. 📊 Analyze Project Characteristics
Size, complexity, type of project

4. ⚙️ Identify Products & Activities
List deliverables (modules, features)
Break into tasks

5. ⏳ Estimate Effort & Time
How much time and work is required

6. 💰 Identify Activity Risks
Find possible risks (delay, cost overrun)

7. 📅 Allocate Resources
Assign team members and tools

8. 🗓️ Schedule Activities
Set timeline and deadlines

9. 📄 Review & Finalize Plan
Check plan and approve

🎯 Importance
Clear step-by-step planning
Better control and management
Reduces errors and risks
